data.chText: 手掌；手心
data.enText: the inner surface of the hand between the wrist and the fingers

data.chText: 他把小鸟轻轻地托在掌心。
data.enText: He held the bird gently in the palm of his hand .

data.chText: 汗涔涔的手掌
data.enText: sweaty palms

data.chText: 看手相
data.enText: to read sb's palm (= to say what you think will happen to sb by looking at the lines on their palm )
palm tree

data.chText: 棕榈树
data.enText: a straight tree with a mass of long leaves at the top, growing in tropical countries. There are several types of palm tree, some of which produce fruit.

data.chText: 枣椰树
data.enText: a date palm

data.chText: 椰子树
data.enText: a coconut palm

data.chText: 棕榈叶 / 树丛
data.enText: palm leaves/fronds/groves
have sb in the palm of your hand

data.chText: 完全控制某人；把某人攥在手心里
data.enText: to have complete control or influence over sb
cross sb's palm with silver

data.chText: 为得到好处而给某人钱；（尤指）付钱请人算命
data.enText: to give sb money so that they will do you a favour, especially tell your fortune
grease sb's palm

data.chText: 向某人行贿；用金钱收买
data.enText: to give sb money in order to persuade them to do sth dishonest

data.chText: 把…藏在手中（尤指玩戏法）
data.enText: to hide a coin, card, etc. in your hand, especially when performing a trick
palm sb↔off (with sth)

data.chText: （借口某事）欺骗搪塞某人，骗过某人
data.enText: to persuade sb to believe an excuse or an explanation that is not true, in order to stop them asking questions or complaining
palm sth↔off (on/onto sb)
palm sb↔off (with sth)

data.chText: 哄骗他人接受（无价值或自己不要的东西）；用假货行骗
data.enText: to persuade sb to accept sth that has no value or that you do not want, especially by tricking them

data.chText: 她总是哄骗她的助手做最苦的差事。
data.enText: She's always palming the worst jobs off on her assistant.

data.chText: 当心别上当让他把残次品卖给你。
data.enText: Make sure he doesn't try to palm you off with faulty goods.
palm sth off as sth

data.chText: 推销假货；以假乱真
data.enText: to tell sb that sth is better than it is, especially in order to sell it

data.chText: 他们在设法把那张普通桌子当真正的古董推销出去。
data.enText: They were trying to palm the table off as a genuine antique.

trans: （用谎话或借口）欺骗搪塞，打发

tr: the inner surface of the hand from the wrist to the base of the fingers
an award for winning a championship or commemorating some other event
any plant of the family Palmae having an unbranched trunk crowned by large pinnate or palmate leaves
a linear unit based on the length or width of the human hand
touch, lift, or hold with the hands

value.def: A palm or a palm tree is a tree that grows in hot countries. It has long leaves growing at the top, and no branches.
The palm of your hand is the inside part.

example.ex: Dornberg slapped the table with the palm of his hand...
example.tran: 多恩伯格用手拍着桌子。
他擦了擦满是汗水的手掌。

value.def: If you have someone or something in the palm of your hand, you have control over them.

example.ex: Johnson thought he had the board of directors in the palm of his hand...
example.tran: 约翰逊以为自己完全掌控了董事会。

example.ex: They held his fate in the palms of their ancient hands.
example.tran: 他们这些老人将他的命运掌握在手心里。

value.tran: 在…的手心里；在…的完全掌控中
